## Complete tool reference

### `log_fix_attempt` — Record and analyze a fix attempt

**Call after:** Every fix attempt (code change, config edit, install, revert, etc.)
**State change:** Yes — records the attempt and may change escalation level
**Parameters:**
| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `error_message` | string | Yes | Full error message with type, body, and key stack trace lines |
| `files_involved` | string[] | Yes | Every file touched in this fix (source, config, test, lockfiles) |
| `fix_description` | string | Yes | Specific description: WHAT changed, WHY, HOW it differs from previous |
| `session_id` | string | No | Isolation ID for parallel tasks. Default: "default" |

**Returns:**
```json
{
  "status": "ok | loop_detected",
  "loop_level": "NONE | NUDGE | WARNING | CRITICAL",
  "attempt_number": 5,
  "similar_attempts": 3,
  "error_category": "type",
  "message": "Human-readable guidance for the AI",
  "strategies": [
    {
      "title": "Strategy name",
      "action": "Specific steps to execute",
      "reasoning": "Why this strategy helps in this situation"
    }
  ],
  "previous_attempts": [
    "#1: Added null check for user object [runtime] (14:23:01)",
    "#2: Wrapped map() call in optional chaining [runtime] (14:24:15)",
    "#3: Added default empty array to useState [runtime] (14:25:30)"
  ]
}
```

**Field meanings:**
- `status`: "ok" = no loop, "loop_detected" = NUDGE or higher
- `loop_level`: Current escalation level for this error
- `attempt_number`: How many times you've hit this same error (same fingerprint)
- `similar_attempts`: How many previous fixes had >55% word overlap with this one (same approach detection)
- `error_category`: Auto-detected category used for strategy matching
- `message`: Guidance text calibrated to the escalation level
- `strategies`: Actionable escape strategies, ordered by relevance (category-specific first, then general). Present only when loop_level != NONE.
- `previous_attempts`: Chronological log of what you've tried before. Present when attempt_number > 1. Use this to ensure your next attempt is genuinely different.

### `check_loop_status` — Read-only status check

**Call before:** Complex multi-file fixes, or to check current state
**State change:** No — purely read-only
**Parameters:**
| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `session_id` | string | No | Session to check. Default: "default" |

**Returns:** Same shape as `log_fix_attempt` response, but without incrementing any counters. `previous_attempts` shows ALL logged attempts for this session.

### `get_escape_strategies` — Get strategies without logging

**Call when:** Planning next move, want category-specific advice
**State change:** No
**Parameters:**
| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `error_category` | enum | No | "syntax" / "type" / "import" / "build" / "test" / "runtime" / "unknown". Auto-detected from last attempt if omitted. |
| `session_id` | string | No | Default: "default" |

**Returns:**
```json
{
  "strategies": [...],
  "error_category": "type",
  "loop_level": "WARNING"
}
```

### `resolve_loop` — Reset tracking after fix

**Call when:** Error is confirmed fixed
**State change:** Yes — clears all attempt history and resets escalation to NONE
**Parameters:**
| Param | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `session_id` | string | No | Session to resolve. Default: "default" |

**Returns:**
```json
{
  "status": "resolved",
  "total_attempts": 5
}
```

